          "The Noviserim are the novices of clerical training, which takes place in scriptoria attached to churches, abbeys, or in the urban Collegia of Egel or Wikkensmeade. A young aspirant is taken into one of the orders at age eleven or twelve, rising through novice ranks through menial tasks, eventually assigned to a cleric as a servant or scribe. The lessons of humility and hierarchy are learned through example. A Novisere can spend much of their adolescence in the service of a cleric before passing to the next rank.",
          "The Serim form the backbone of the Covenant — the clerics, holy warriors, and guardians who tend churches and shrines all across the north. Each Sere is required to seek inspiration from at least one Divine through whom their devotions pass to Aeladh. In prestigious areas, a cleric might be one of dozens responsible for upkeep of the faith. In a rural backwater, a single cleric might be responsible for travel across an area containing many shrines, required to defend the faith with both sermon and sword.",
          "In circumstances where a cleric is recognised by the Serirmot for inspirational leadership or wisdom, they may be promoted to Aldsere — a Senior Cleric. With such a promotion comes entry to the Serirmot, the council of clerics, and significant spiritual authority over the knights and lords of the region. The position of Ald is hotly contested between the holy orders eager to increase their influence over the Serirmot.",
          "The Serimot is an ancient gathering of senior clerics, called once every year for the agreement of articles of faith, the settling of disputes, high-profile appointments or excommunications, and the formal agreement of holy war. Only the Ald are permitted to sit, discuss, and vote. The Serimot meets in the Basilica nRos at Muhr-i-nRos, but more recently has also met in the Grand Palace at Egel due to conflicts in the region of the Red Abbey.",
          "Ossere is the most senior position a cleric can attain in any one order. An Ossere is responsible for the discipline and well-being of the Aldserim below them, protecting the faith at a strategic level in an area equivalent to a ducal domain. They oversee a retinue of Allegiant Guard and often a significant military levy. In times of stability there are usually 20–30 Ossere in the north, spread from the Ulla Coast to the borders of the Ilantha.",
          "The Awensere is the spiritual head of the Covenant, taking the official titles of Commander of the Allegiant Guard, Confessor to Kings, Guardian of the Red Abbey, and Supreme Servant of Aeladh. The Awensere is bestowed by the Serimot upon their chosen Ossere, with executive control of all matters of the church — promotion of spiritual practice, spending of tithes, and proclamation of anathema. The current Awensere is Her Holiness Magrethe, Second of Her Name.",
