          "Enforcement of Covenant power and discipline is carried out by the Orders Militant — the fighting soldiers of the Covenant. Each divine order maintains a force under arms to defend the chapels and villages over whom the Covenant offers protection. Brothers and sisters rise through ranks similar to those of a feudal retinue, from Squires through Companions to Knight Companions and Knight Commanders.",
          "The Allegiant Guard is an elite chivalric order operating under the direct command of the higher ranks of the Covenant. Its primary purpose is to protect the lives of the higher ranks, and to protect the kings, queens, and their heirs in lands which profess allegiance to Aeladh. Entry to the Allegiant Guard is through recommendation followed by a secret quest or errand in which personal loyalty, ability, and behaviour is tested. Upon induction, each soldier renounces formal ties to their order, with sole loyalty to the Awensere.",
          "Knights of the Allegiant are typically armed with a polearm carrying their personal heraldry, a sword dedicated with the symbol of Aeladh, the finest lobstered plate steel armour available, a white tabard bearing the arms of the Awensere, and a cloak trimmed with white winter furs. Their greatest concentration is at Egel and Muhr-i-nRos, where chapters of some six hundred knights guard Covenant buildings, the Awensere, and King Aeden of the Hart.",
