          "Whilst the soldiers protect and the clerics preach, the spies, diplomats, and inquisitors of the Covenant attend to duties the Awensere would rather keep hidden. These are performed by the Keepers of the Word — a chapter of clerics, monks, heralds, and, if required, assassins, who owe their personal loyalty to the Awensere. Membership is by invitation through recommendation, after a long period during which the candidate is investigated. Candidates are often expected to discern that the order is interested in their skills without the order explicitly stating so.",
          "Duties of the Keepers are broad. They investigate internal threats to the church such as corruption and abuse of power among the three branches, reporting directly to the Awensere where they cannot solve the matter themselves. They investigate threats from external sources, including rival kings or lords, and clerics of other faiths. Of particular current concern is the ongoing presence of Kainan agents and the infiltration of society by Baalphegorite clerics. Some agents are also tasked with discovering ways to increase the strength of the church in foreign lands.",
